  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, on the Amazon-Book dataset, BERT4Rec 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 's performance is comparable to its baseline version.",
    "While language models can generally augment recommendation tasks, addressing the disparity between semantic and behavioral spaces remains challenging.",
    "• For LLM-controlled RS approaches, such as Chat-REC and LLM-Rank, they couldn't achieve consistent improvements over SAS-Rec in the same way as ToolRec.",
    "This suggests that merely using basic control strategies or employing LLM as a ranker might not be the most effective way forward for recommendation tasks.A more comprehensive strategy, as demonstrated by ToolRec, appears better suited to harnessing LLMs to enhance recommendations.Table 2: The test performance comparison on three real-world datasets.",
    "The bold font denotes the winner in that column."
